<L>__{interior castle hackton brookside's room day}
<A>__{brookside smashing a chair over the head of his governor, reverend hunt.}
<C>__{roderick }
<D>__{twice or thrice, reverend hunt attempted to punish my lord brookside; but i promise you the rogue was too strong for him, and leveled the oxford man to the ground with a chair, greatly to the delight of little patrick, who cried out: "bravo, brooksy! thump him, thump him!"}
<L>__{exterior castle hackton garden day}
<A>__{brookside and patrick.}
<C>__{roderick }
<D>__{with the child, brookside was, strange to say, pretty tractable. he took a liking to the little fellow i like him the more, he said, because he was "half a cosgrove."}
